GOLDEN RULES OF ACCOUNTING:
- Personal Account:  Debit the Receiver  | Credit the Giver
- Real Account:      Debit what comes IN  | Credit what goes OUT
- Nominal Account:   Debit Expenses/Losses | Credit Incomes/Gains

FUNDAMENTAL ACCOUNTING EQUATION: Assets = Liabilities + Capital (Owner's Equity)

DEPRECIATION METHODS:
Straight Line Method (SLM):
  Annual Depreciation = (Cost − Salvage/Scrap Value) ÷ Useful Life in years
  SLM Rate % = (Annual Dep ÷ Original Cost) × 100

Written Down Value Method (WDV):
  Annual Depreciation = Opening WDV × Depreciation Rate %
  WDV Rate = [1 − (Salvage/Cost)^(1/Life)] × 100
  (WDV method results in higher depreciation in early years)

