RATIO ANALYSIS — Key Ratios:
LIQUIDITY:
  Current Ratio     = Current Assets ÷ Current Liabilities  (Ideal: 2:1)
  Quick/Acid Ratio  = (CA − Inventory − Prepaid) ÷ CL       (Ideal: 1:1)
  Cash Ratio        = (Cash + Bank) ÷ CL

PROFITABILITY:
  Gross Profit %    = (Gross Profit ÷ Net Sales) × 100
  Net Profit %      = (Net Profit after Tax ÷ Net Sales) × 100
  EBITDA Margin     = EBITDA ÷ Revenue × 100
  ROE               = Net Profit ÷ Shareholder Equity × 100
  ROCE              = EBIT ÷ Capital Employed × 100
  ROA               = Net Profit ÷ Total Assets × 100

SOLVENCY:
  Debt-Equity Ratio  = Long-term Debt ÷ Shareholders Equity  (Ideal: < 2:1)
  Interest Coverage  = EBIT ÷ Interest Expense                (Ideal: > 3x)
  Proprietary Ratio  = Equity ÷ Total Assets

ACTIVITY / EFFICIENCY:
  Inventory Turnover = COGS ÷ Average Inventory
  Debtor Turnover    = Net Credit Sales ÷ Average Debtors
  Creditor Turnover  = Net Credit Purchases ÷ Average Creditors
  Asset Turnover     = Net Sales ÷ Total Assets

BANK RECONCILIATION STATEMENT (BRS):
Balance as per Bank Statement (Pass Book)
(+) Deposits in transit (recorded in cash book, not yet credited by bank)
(−) Outstanding cheques (issued by us, not yet presented to bank)
(+) Bank charges not yet recorded in cash book
(−) Bank interest/receipts credited by bank but not in cash book
(±) Errors in bank statement or cash book
= Adjusted Balance (must match Cash Book balance)

