EMPLOYEES' PROVIDENT FUND (EPF) — EPF Act 1952:
Applicability: Establishments with 20+ employees
- Employee contribution: 12% of (Basic + DA)
- Employer contribution: 12% of (Basic + DA), split as:
  * 8.33% → EPS (Employees Pension Scheme) [capped on ₹15,000 basis]
  * 3.67% → EPF account of employee
- Employer also pays: 0.50% EDLI + 0.50% admin charges
Due date for deposit: 15th of the following month
Employee contribution exceeding 12%: Goes to VPF (Voluntary PF), same tax benefits
Interest rate on EPF: Declared annually (currently ~8.25% p.a., tax-free on withdrawal after 5 yrs)

EMPLOYEES' STATE INSURANCE (ESI) — ESI Act 1948:
Applicability: Establishments with 10+ employees, gross salary ≤ ₹21,000/month
- Employee contribution: 0.75% of gross wages
- Employer contribution: 3.25% of gross wages
Due date: 15th of the following month
Benefits: Medical, disability, maternity, dependant benefits

