TAX AUDIT — SECTION 44AB
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

TAX AUDIT MANDATORY WHEN:
- Business turnover > ₹1 Crore [EXCEPTION: > ₹10 Crore if ≥ 95% cash receipts AND 95% cash payments are digital]
- Professional receipts > ₹50 Lakhs
- Opted presumptive u/s 44AD but declared income < 8% (cash) or 6% (digital) of turnover
- Opted presumptive u/s 44ADA but declared income < 50% of gross receipts
- Opted presumptive u/s 44AE but declared income less than prescribed
- Brought forward losses claimed, where books of accounts maintained

FORMS:
- Form 3CA + 3CD: When accounts are already audited under Companies Act or other law
- Form 3CB + 3CD: When NOT required to be audited under any other law
- Auditor must be a practicing Chartered Accountant (FCA or ACA)
Due date: 30 September of the assessment year
Penalty for non-compliance: 0.5% of turnover or ₹1,50,000 whichever is LOWER (u/s 271B)

PRESUMPTIVE TAXATION SCHEMES:
- 44AD (Business, not profession): Declare 8% of turnover (6% for digital receipts) as profit. No books required.
  Eligible: Individual, HUF, Partnership firm. Turnover ≤ ₹3 Crore (if 95%+ receipts digital) else ≤ ₹2 Crore.
- 44ADA (Profession): Declare 50% of gross receipts as profit. Eligible professionals only (doctors, lawyers, CAs, engineers etc.)
  Receipt limit: ≤ ₹75 Lakhs (if 95%+ receipts digital) else ≤ ₹50 Lakhs.
- 44AE (Transport): Fixed profit per vehicle per month. Own ≤ 10 goods vehicles.

