━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

EMI FORMULA:
EMI = [P × r × (1+r)^n] ÷ [(1+r)^n − 1]
Where: P = Principal | r = Monthly interest rate (Annual%÷12÷100) | n = Tenure in months
Total interest paid = (EMI × n) − P

BREAK-EVEN ANALYSIS:
Break-even Units = Fixed Cost ÷ (Selling Price per unit − Variable Cost per unit)
Break-even Sales  = Fixed Cost ÷ P/V Ratio
P/V Ratio         = Contribution Margin ÷ Sales × 100
Contribution      = Sales − Total Variable Costs
Margin of Safety  = Actual Sales − Break-even Sales

NPV (Net Present Value):
NPV = Σ [Net Cash Flow at time t ÷ (1+discount rate)^t] − Initial Investment
Decision: NPV > 0 → Accept | NPV < 0 → Reject | NPV = 0 → Indifferent/Break-even

IRR (Internal Rate of Return):
Rate at which NPV = 0. If IRR > Cost of Capital → Accept

WORKING CAPITAL MANAGEMENT:
Working Capital = Current Assets − Current Liabilities
Operating Cycle = Inventory Days + Debtor Days − Creditor Days
Cash Conversion Cycle = DIO + DSO − DPO

